headlines.description: — De'Andre Hunter's three-point play with 1:07 remaining put Atlanta ahead to stay, and the Hawks held off the Washington Wizards 122-120 on Wednesday night despite a career-high 43 points by Kristaps Porzingis.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks edge Wizards 122-120 despite Porzingis' 43 points

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 30 points and made six 3-pointers, and the Boston Celtics beat the Portland Trail Blazers 115-93 to snap a three-game losing streak Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 30 to help Celtics power past Blazers 115-93

headlines.description: — Cleveland coach J.B. Bickerstaff called it grit. Miami coach Erik Spoelstra called it disruptiveness.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 25 points, Cavaliers hold off Heat 104-100

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum stopped suddenly near the left sideline, dribbled between his legs, behind his back and then crossed over to create enough space to let fly a 3-pointer that New Orleans absolutely needed to avoid a late meltdown.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum scores 32, Pelicans hold off Mavericks 113-106

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 25 points and 15 rebounds, Zach LaVine scored 29 points on 12-of-18 shooting and the Chicago Bulls gave their playoff hopes an unexpected boost with a 117-96 victory against the Western Conference-leading Denver Nuggets on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic, LaVine lead Bulls to 117-96 win over Nuggets

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant's expected home debut was over before it started after a pregame mishap.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Ross help Suns rout Thunder after Durant injured

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 24 points, Paul George had 23 and the Los Angeles Clippers broke away in the second half to beat the Toronto Raptors 108-100 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers pull away in second half to beat Raptors 108-100
